"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is designed to retrieve data from the table named 'defaultview-545'. It calculates the count of 'CASE_ID' and labels it as 'No. of Cases'. It also calculates the average cycle time between the 'Approve PR item' event and the 'Create PO Item' event by subtracting the first occurrence of 'END_TIME' where 'EVENT_NAME' equals 'Approve PR item' from the last occurrence of 'END_TIME' where 'EVENT_NAME' equals 'Create PO Item'. This average cycle time is labeled as 'Avg. Cycle Time (PR Apprvl to Crt PO)'. The query also selects the 'PO Business Unit' column. The results are ordered in descending order based on the 'No. of Cases' and only the top 100 records are returned."
